Source: waveshare-ups
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Jaco Hanekom <jhanekom@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13),
               cmake
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: waveshare-ups
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Waveshare UPS HAT (B) I2C telemetry publisher
 Reads the Waveshare UPS HAT (B) battery management board via I2C
 (INA219 power monitor chip) and broadcasts one JSON telemetry line
 per poll cycle over TCP.
 .
 Reports bus voltage, current, power, shunt voltage, estimated state
 of charge, charging status, and online state. Configurable poll
 interval, I2C address, shunt resistor value, and battery voltage
 thresholds.
 .
 Data stream  : TCP :<8564>  (newline-delimited JSON)
 Status query : TCP :<8565>  (echo status | nc localhost 8565)
 Config       : /etc/waveshare-ups/config.ini
